/-! ## B6 вҖ” local Tate duality (per-`n` bundle, at every finite `k/в„ҡвӮӮ`)

The dual module `MuDual n M = Hom(M, ОјвӮҷ)` (conjugation action), the evaluation cup pairing,
the group-parametric bundle `TateDualityG G n` (with `TateDuality n` = the `G_в„ҡвӮӮ` member), and
the gate `IsLocalDualizingGroup` вҖ” with the encoding decisions and flagged deviations (per-`n`
form, `в„Ө/n`-valued Pontryagin duals, single currying, unnormalized `inv`) вҖ” are defined in
`GQ2/TateDuality.lean`; its stress tests are parametrized over an arbitrary bundle and are
therefore axiom-free. -/

/-- **The B6 axiom (base-generalized to all finite `k/в„ҡвӮӮ`).** Local Tate duality at any local
Galois group `G` over `в„ҡвӮӮ` (`G_в„ҡвӮӮ` or an open finite-index subgroup `G_K`, `K/в„ҡвӮӮ` finite вҖ” the
`IsLocalDualizingGroup` hypothesis): an invariant map `inv : HВІ(G, ОјвӮҷ) вүғ+ в„Ө/n` making the
evaluation cup pairings `HвҒұ(G, Hom(M, ОјвӮҷ)) Г— H^{2вҲ’i}(G, M) вҶ’ HВІ(G, ОјвӮҷ) вү… в„Ө/n` perfect for every
finite discrete `n`-torsion `G`-module `M`, in the three degree pairs `(0,2)`, `(1,1)`, `(2,0)`.

NSW (7.2.6) states Tate duality for arbitrary `p`-adic `k`, so the interface is parametrized by a
local dualizing group rather than restricted to `в„ҡвӮӮ`.  The base member `k = в„ҡвӮӮ` is the
in-repository definition `GQ2.tateDuality` below.

Citation: **NSW [1], Ch. VII В§7.2, Theorem (7.2.6)** (local Tate duality, for any `p`-adic `k`);
Serre, *Galois Cohomology* II В§5.2, Theorem 2; Milne, *ADT* I.2.3.  Induced mod-2 Hilbert-pairing
nondegeneracy over `G_K`: FV Ch. IV В§5 Prop (5.1)(6)/Cor./Thm (5.2), O'Meara
ITQF 63:13.  Paper: В§В§5вҖ“8 (the `рқ”ҪвӮӮ` dimension counts) and В§6.3;
`docs/literature-axioms.md` B6, `docs/orchestration/p15f7-axiom-proposal.md`. -/
axiom tateDualityAt (G : Type) [Group G] [TopologicalSpace G] [IsTopologicalGroup G]
    (n : в„•) [NeZero n] [DistribMulAction G (MuN n)] [ContinuousSMul G (MuN n)]
    (hloc : IsLocalDualizingGroup G n) : TateDualityG G n

/-- **B6 at the base field `в„ҡвӮӮ`** вҖ” the `G = G_в„ҡвӮӮ` member of `tateDualityAt`, using
`isLocalDualizingGroup_absGalQ2`. -/
noncomputable def tateDuality (n : в„•) [NeZero n] : TateDuality n :=
  tateDualityAt AbsGalQ2 n (isLocalDualizingGroup_absGalQ2 n)

/-! ## B8 вҖ” the cyclotomic action on peripheral generators (Lemma 3.6)

The concrete group `О” = maxPro2(FreeProfinite (Fin 2))`, its peripheral generators `P, T, C`, and
the bundle `PeripheralCyclotomicAction` вҖ” with the flagged faithfulness deviation (the literal
statement is about the outer action on an Г©tale/anabelian `ПҖвӮҒ`, absent from Mathlib) and the pinning
of the exponent embedding `О№` вҖ” are defined in `GQ2/PeripheralAction.lean`. -/

/-- **[Composite вҖ” B8.]** Local cyclotomic action on the peripheral inertia generators of
`О” = ПҖвӮҒ^{pro-2}(в„ҷВ№ вҲ– {0,1,вҲһ})`: for every `u вҲҲ в„ӨвӮӮЛЈ` there is a continuous automorphism `ПҶ_u` of `О”`
sending each peripheral generator to a cyclotomic conjugate, `ПҶ_u(P) = c_PвҒ»В№ В· P^u В· c_P` (and
likewise `T`, `C`), the `u`-th power via бә‘-exponentiation.  This is Lemma 3.6's group-theoretic
conclusion; see `GQ2/PeripheralAction.lean` for the deviation from the literal `ПҖвӮҒ` statement.

**This is a composite leaf, not Stix alone** (`docs/adversarial-axioms-review.md` В§1).  Stix
supports that the decomposition group acts on
cuspidal inertia *through the cyclotomic character*; producing an automorphism for **every**
`u вҲҲ в„ӨвӮӮЛЈ` вҖ” the `aut : в„Ө_[2]ЛЈ вҶ’ ContinuousMulEquiv О” О”` field, quantified over all units вҖ”
additionally needs a **cyclotomic-surjectivity** input (a decomposition-group element realizing
each `u`).  Locally, B5 supplies this through `ПҮ_cyc(rec u) = uвҒ»В№` and dense reciprocity image.
B8 keeps the all-units form because that is the interface consumed by Lemma 3.6.

Citation: **Stix [8], В§3.3 + Definition 37** (cuspidal inertia acts through the cyclotomic
character вҖ” the paper's exact citation) together with local cyclotomic surjectivity from B5;
classical origin Deligne, MSRI 16 (1989).  Paper: Lemma 3.6.  `docs/literature-axioms.md` B8. -/
axiom peripheralCyclotomicAction : PeripheralCyclotomicAction

/-! ## B9 вҖ” the relative StiefelвҖ“Whitney identity (paper eq. (111)), degrees вүӨ 2

Since the B9-A flip (2026-07-24, `docs/orchestration/b9a-proof-plan.md`) the B9 leaf is the
**relative StiefelвҖ“Whitney identity** at the quadratic-form level: the left-hand sides are
genuine isometry-class invariants (`swOne`/`swTwo`, `GQ2/StiefelWhitney.lean`, with Delzant
well-definedness **proved**, not scoped away), evaluated on the twisted trace forms
`Tr_{k(Оҙ)/k}вҹЁaвҹ©` of `GQ2/TraceForm.lean`.  The previous composite axiom statement вҖ” eq. (111)
at the fixed Lemma 6.16 diagonalizations вҖ” is now the same-name **theorem** `evensKahn_dyadic`
below (placed after B11a, which its proof consumes), derived via `evensKahn_dyadic_of_rsw`
(`GQ2/EvensKahnDerived.lean`); consumers were untouched.  The cocycle-level ingredients
(`corH1`, `evensNormH2`, `kummerClassK`) are unchanged from `GQ2/EvensKahn.lean`. -/

/-- **The B9 axiom вҖ” the relative StiefelвҖ“Whitney identity** (Kahn, Invent. Math. 78 (1984),
ThГ©orГЁme 2 at the rank-1 form `вҹЁaвҹ©`, expanded through Evens Thm 1 / Kozlowski Thm 1.1 at
index 2; paper eq. (111), degrees вүӨ 2), over an arbitrary **finite dyadic base** `k`.

Setting: `k/в„ҡвӮӮ` finite inside the fixed `в„ҡМ„вӮӮ`; `d вҲҲ kЛЈ` with `ОҙВІ = d`; `L = k(Оҙ) = quadExt k Оҙ`,
quadratic over `k` (`hdeg` вҖ” provable from `hidx`/`hUo` via `finrank_quadExt_eq_two`, but
carried so the statement is locally Kahn's `L/k` setting, per the owner's Q1 decision);
`G_L вҲ© G_k` is the stabilizer subgroup of `Оҙ` (the verbatim pre-flip encoding: `hidx`, `s`,
`hs`, `htriv`, `hUo`); `a вҲҲ LЛЈ` **arbitrary**, entering degree-wise through the Kummer
1-cocycle `Оұ` of a square root `ОІ` of `a` (`hОІ`/`hОІ0`/`hОұdef`/`hОұ`/`hОұc`).  With `wвӮҒ = swOne k`
and `wвӮӮ = swTwo k htriv` the StiefelвҖ“Whitney classes of `GQ2/StiefelWhitney.lean`, the two
components of Kahn's identity `w(TrвҹЁaвҹ©) = w(TrвҹЁ1вҹ©)В·(1 + cor[a] + N^{Ev}[a])` read:

* degree 1: `wвӮҒ(TrвҹЁaвҹ©) = wвӮҒ(TrвҹЁ1вҹ©) + cor[a]`;
* degree 2: `wвӮӮ(TrвҹЁaвҹ©) = wвӮӮ(TrвҹЁ1вҹ©) + wвӮҒ(TrвҹЁ1вҹ©) вҢЈ cor[a] + N^{Ev}[a]`.

The cited theorems hold over any field of characteristic different from `2` (Kahn Th. 2 requires
no local hypothesis), while the paper invokes (111) over finite dyadic bases; the interface is
therefore base-general within the dyadic setting.  Deviations (flagged): truncation to degrees
вүӨ 2; `N^{Ev}` *defined* by the two-point graph cocycle (98) (`evensNormH2`, Lemma 6.13); finite
dyadic base.  Removed relative to the pre-flip axiom: the Lemma 6.16 diagonalization scoping.

Citation: Kahn, Invent. Math. 78 (1984), ThГ©orГЁme 2 (with ThГ©orГЁme 1); Kozlowski, Proc. AMS
91 (1984), Thm 1.1; Evens, Trans. AMS 108 (1963), Thm 1.  Paper: В§6, eq. (111),
Lemmas 6.13/6.16.  `docs/literature-axioms.md` B9; census swap user-approved 2026-07-24
(`docs/orchestration/b9a-tickets.md`, T5 gate). -/
axiom relativeStiefelWhitney_dyadic
    (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])) [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k]
    (d : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ)
    (Оҙ ОІ : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])
    (hОҙ : Оҙ ^ 2 = ((d : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    (hdeg : Module.finrank вҶҘk вҶҘ(quadExt k Оҙ) = 2)
    (a : (вҶҘ(quadExt k Оҙ))ЛЈ)
    (hОІ : ОІ ^ 2 = ((a : вҶҘ(quadExt k Оҙ)) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    (hОІ0 : ОІ вү  0)
    (hidx : ((MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf
        k.fixingSubgroup).index = 2)
    (s : k.fixingSubgroup)
    (hs : s вҲү (MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf k.fixingSubgroup)
    (htriv : вҲҖ (g : k.fixingSubgroup) (m : ZMod 2), g вҖў m = m)
    (hUo : IsOpen (((MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf
        k.fixingSubgroup : Subgroup k.fixingSubgroup) : Set k.fixingSubgroup))
    (Оұ : ((MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf
        k.fixingSubgroup) вҶ’ ZMod 2)
    (hОұdef : вҲҖ g, Оұ g = Kummer.kummerCocycleFun ОІ
        ((g : k.fixingSubgroup) : Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]))
    (hОұ : вҲҖ g h, Оұ (g * h) = Оұ g + Оұ h)
    (hОұc : Continuous Оұ) :
    (swOne k (traceFormTwisted k Оҙ вҶ‘a)
      = swOne k (traceFormOne k Оҙ) + corH1 htriv hUo hidx hs Оұ hОұ hОұc)
    вҲ§ (swTwo k htriv (traceFormTwisted k Оҙ вҶ‘a)
