/-! ## B11 вҖ” the dyadic norm criterion over finite bases

Section 6.3 uses the norm criterion and unit-norm surjectivity over arbitrary finite dyadic bases.
The interface separates the remaining classical axiom B11a from the spectral-norm convention and
the in-repository proof of unramified unit-norm surjectivity.  The combined
`dyadicNormCriterion` theorem below preserves the paired interface for consumers:

* `hilbertSymbol_normCriterion_finiteDyadic` вҖ” the symbol/norm criterion (classical).
* `unramifiedQuadratic_units_are_norms` вҖ” units of an unramified quadratic extension are norms
  (classical).
* `HasEqualNormValueGroups` (named `IsUnramifiedQuadraticSpectral` before 2026-07-24) вҖ” **not an
  axiom**: the repo's spectral-norm *working criterion* for "`k(Оҙa)/k` is unramified" (equal norm
  value groups on `в„ҡМ„вӮӮ`, i.e. `e = 1`).  Isolated here as the review's "riskiest piece": it is a
  project convention, not a Mathlib unramifiedness notion, and is deliberately a `def` (asserting
  nothing) rather than a bridge axiom.

Encoding conventions carried over from the pre-split axiom: the "`b` is a norm from `k(вҲҡa)`"
condition is the **norm form** `b = xВІ вҲ’ a yВІ` (elementary, no relative field-extension
plumbing); unramifiedness by **equal norm value groups** through the spectral norm on `в„ҡМ„вӮӮ` (the
`GQ2/SectionSix.lean` `IsDeepUnit`/`lemma_6_16` convention).

Note for reviewers: the Steinberg relation `[x]вҲӘ[1вҲ’x] = 0` and `[2]вҲӘ[вҲ’1] = 0` used in
Lemma 6.16's proof are *consequences* of the criterion clause (norm representations
`1 вҲ’ x = 1ВІ вҲ’ xВ·1ВІ` and `вҲ’1 = 1ВІ вҲ’ 2В·1ВІ`), so they are deliberately not separate clauses.

Citation: Serre, *Local Fields* [7], Ch. XIV В§2, Proposition 4(iii) (the symbolвҖ“norm criterion;
over `в„ҡ_p` also CiA [CiA] Ch. III В§1.1 Prop. 1), and Ch. V В§2 (norms of unramified extensions
are the units times the norms of uniformizers).  Paper: В§6.3, displays (93)/(94) and Lemma 6.16.
-/

/-- **Equal norm value groups for `k(Оҙa)/k` вҖ” the project's unramifiedness criterion.**  Every
nonzero `z = x + yВ·Оҙa` (`x, y вҲҲ k`) has the same norm as some nonzero element of the base `k`,
i.e. `k(Оҙa)` and `k` have equal norm value groups.  For a quadratic extension of complete
discretely valued fields this says `e(k(Оҙa)/k) = 1`, the standard unramifiedness criterion
(Serre, *Local Fields*, Ch. I В§4); the definition is named by what it literally asserts because
the equivalence with a bona-fide ramification-theoretic notion is *not* proved here (no Mathlib
ramification theory applies at these types yet вҖ” `IsNonarchimedeanLocalField` has no
extension/ramification layer as of 2026-07-24).  This is **not** a Mathlib unramifiedness notion
and is asserted by nothing (it is a `def`, not an axiom); it is the convention the В§6 ledger
consumes, named and isolated per adversarial review rec 2 so a human reviewer can see exactly
where the project departs from a directly citable statement.  Named
`IsUnramifiedQuadraticSpectral` before 2026-07-24 (deprecated alias below). -/
def HasEqualNormValueGroups
    (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    (Оҙa : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) : Prop :=
  вҲҖ z : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2], z вү  0 вҶ’
    (вҲғ x y : вҶҘk, z = (x : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) + (y : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) * Оҙa) вҶ’
    вҲғ w : вҶҘk, w вү  0 вҲ§ вҖ–zвҖ– = вҖ–(w : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])вҖ–

@[deprecated HasEqualNormValueGroups (since := "2026-07-24")]
alias IsUnramifiedQuadraticSpectral := HasEqualNormValueGroups

/-- **[Classical вҖ” B11a.]**  The dyadic Hilbert-symbol **norm criterion** over a finite base
`k/в„ҡвӮӮ`, in Kummer-cup form: for `a, b вҲҲ kЛЈ`, `[a] вҲӘ [b] = 0` in `HВІ(G_k, рқ”ҪвӮӮ)` iff `b` is a norm
from `k(вҲҡa)` вҖ” iff `b = xВІ вҲ’ a yВІ` has a solution in `k` (for `a` a square the norm form is
universal, so no non-square hypothesis is needed).

Citation: Serre, *Local Fields* [7], Ch. XIV В§2, Proposition 4(iii) (symbol vanishes iff the
second entry is a norm), Proposition 5 (the symbol is the cup product), and Proposition 7(iii)
(the multiplicative-root-of-unity form); over `в„ҡ_p` also CiA Ch. III В§1.1 Prop. 1.
Paper: В§6.3 (norm-criterion input to the local square-class calculation). -/
axiom hilbertSymbol_normCriterion_finiteDyadic
    (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])) [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k]
    (htriv : вҲҖ (g : k.fixingSubgroup) (m : ZMod 2), g вҖў m = m) :
    вҲҖ a b : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ,
      kummerClassK k a вҢЈ[htriv] kummerClassK k b = 0
        вҶ” вҲғ x y : вҶҘk, (b : вҶҘk) = x ^ 2 - (a : вҶҘk) * y ^ 2

/-! ### B9, derived form (placed after B11a, which the proof consumes) -/

/-- **Formerly the B9 axiom вҖ” since 2026-07-24 a derived theorem** (the B9-A flip; the statement
is byte-identical to the pre-flip axiom, zero consumer churn вҖ” the B7вҖІ/B11b/B12/B13 pattern).
Eq. (111) at the paper's Lemma 6.16 diagonalizations `Tr_{L/k}вҹЁaвҹ© вүғ вҹЁ2u, 2dn/uвҹ©`,
`Tr_{L/k}вҹЁ1вҹ© вүғ вҹЁ2, 2dвҹ©`, with `wвӮҒвҹЁx,yвҹ© = [x]+[y]` and `wвӮӮвҹЁx,yвҹ© = [x] вҢЈ [y]`:

* degree 1: `[2u] + [2dn/u] = [2] + [2d] + cor[a]`;
* degree 2: `[2u] вҢЈ [2dn/u] = [2] вҢЈ [2d] + ([2] + [2d]) вҢЈ cor[a] + N^{Ev}[a]`.

Proof: `evensKahn_dyadic_of_rsw` (`GQ2/EvensKahnDerived.lean`) applied to the B9 axiom
`relativeStiefelWhitney_dyadic` and to B11a (the `hnorm` input of the Delzant well-definedness
layer); the T2 trace-form diagonalizations and the proved `swOne`/`swTwo` invariance do the
rewriting.  `#print axioms`: `relativeStiefelWhitney_dyadic` and
`hilbertSymbol_normCriterion_finiteDyadic` (+ the standard three).  Full setting and citations:
the B9 axiom's docstring above and `docs/literature-axioms.md` В§B9. -/
theorem evensKahn_dyadic
    (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])) [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k]
    (u n d : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ) (v : вҶҘk)
    (hn : (n : вҶҘk) = (u : вҶҘk) ^ 2 - (d : вҶҘk) * v ^ 2)
    (Оҙ ОІ : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])
    (hОҙ : Оҙ ^ 2 = ((d : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    (hОІ : ОІ ^ 2 = ((u : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) + (v : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) * Оҙ)
    (hОІ0 : ОІ вү  0)
    (hidx : ((MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf
        k.fixingSubgroup).index = 2)
    (s : k.fixingSubgroup)
    (hs : s вҲү (MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf k.fixingSubgroup)
    (htriv : вҲҖ (g : k.fixingSubgroup) (m : ZMod 2), g вҖў m = m)
    (hUo : IsOpen (((MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf
        k.fixingSubgroup : Subgroup k.fixingSubgroup) : Set k.fixingSubgroup))
    (Оұ : ((MulAction.stabilizer (Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]) Оҙ).subgroupOf
        k.fixingSubgroup) вҶ’ ZMod 2)
    (hОұdef : вҲҖ g, Оұ g = Kummer.kummerCocycleFun ОІ
        ((g : k.fixingSubgroup) : Kummer.GaloisGroup в„ҡ_[2]))
    (hОұ : вҲҖ g h, Оұ (g * h) = Оұ g + Оұ h)
    (hОұc : Continuous Оұ) :
    (kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * u) + kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * d * n * uвҒ»В№)
      = kummerClassK k (twoUnit k) + kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * d)
        + corH1 htriv hUo hidx hs Оұ hОұ hОұc)
    вҲ§ (kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * u) вҢЈ[htriv] kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * d * n * uвҒ»В№)
      = kummerClassK k (twoUnit k) вҢЈ[htriv] kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * d)
        + (kummerClassK k (twoUnit k) + kummerClassK k (twoUnit k * d)) вҢЈ[htriv]
            corH1 htriv hUo hidx hs Оұ hОұ hОұc
        + evensNormH2 htriv hUo hidx hs Оұ hОұ hОұc) :=
  evensKahn_dyadic_of_rsw relativeStiefelWhitney_dyadic k u n d v hn Оҙ ОІ hОҙ hОІ hОІ0 hidx s hs
    htriv hUo Оұ hОұdef hОұ hОұc (hilbertSymbol_normCriterion_finiteDyadic k htriv)

/-- **Unramified unit-norm surjectivity, formerly interface B11b.**  If
`k(вҲҡa)/k` is unramified (the `HasEqualNormValueGroups` convention on a chosen root `Оҙa`,
`ОҙaВІ = a`), then every unit of `k` (`вҖ–uвҖ– = 1`) is a norm from `k(вҲҡa)` вҖ” i.e. `u = xВІ вҲ’ a yВІ` is
solvable in `k`.

Citation: Serre, *Local Fields* [7], Ch. V В§2 (norms of unramified
extensions are the units times the norms of uniformizers).  Paper: В§6.3 (unramified-norm input to
the local calculation).

The proof in `GQ2/UnramifiedQuadraticNorms.lean` completes the square using the involution
`ПғОҙ = вҲ’Оҙ`, then constructs a depth-by-depth norm-form approximation
`wвӮҷвӮҠвӮҒ = wвӮҷ(1 + ПҖвҒҝвҒәВ№zвӮҖ)` against the dyadic unit filtration.  Exact trace coverage
`z вҶҰ z + Пғz` supplies each increment. -/
theorem unramifiedQuadratic_units_are_norms
    (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])) [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k]
    (a : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ) (Оҙa : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])
    (hОҙa : Оҙa ^ 2 = ((a : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    (hunram : HasEqualNormValueGroups k Оҙa) :
    вҲҖ u : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ, вҖ–((u : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])вҖ– = 1 вҶ’
      вҲғ x y : вҶҘk, (u : вҶҘk) = x ^ 2 - (a : вҶҘk) * y ^ 2 :=
  UnramifiedQuadraticNorms.unramifiedQuadratic_units_are_norms' k a Оҙa hОҙa hunram

/-- **The combined dyadic norm criterion.**  This theorem pairs the classical B11a leaf with the
proved unramified-unit theorem.  The equal-norm-value-groups convention remains isolated in
`HasEqualNormValueGroups` (named `IsUnramifiedQuadraticSpectral` before 2026-07-24), which is a
definition rather than an axiom. -/
theorem dyadicNormCriterion
    (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])) [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k]
    (htriv : вҲҖ (g : k.fixingSubgroup) (m : ZMod 2), g вҖў m = m) :
    (вҲҖ a b : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ,
      kummerClassK k a вҢЈ[htriv] kummerClassK k b = 0
        вҶ” вҲғ x y : вҶҘk, (b : вҶҘk) = x ^ 2 - (a : вҶҘk) * y ^ 2)
    вҲ§ вҲҖ (a : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ) (Оҙa : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]),
        Оҙa ^ 2 = ((a : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) вҶ’
        (вҲҖ z : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2], z вү  0 вҶ’
          (вҲғ x y : вҶҘk, z = (x : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) + (y : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]) * Оҙa) вҶ’
          вҲғ w : вҶҘk, w вү  0 вҲ§ вҖ–zвҖ– = вҖ–(w : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])вҖ–) вҶ’
        вҲҖ u : (вҶҘk)ЛЈ, вҖ–((u : вҶҘk) : AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2])вҖ– = 1 вҶ’
          вҲғ x y : вҶҘk, (u : вҶҘk) = x ^ 2 - (a : вҶҘk) * y ^ 2 :=
  вҹЁhilbertSymbol_normCriterion_finiteDyadic k htriv,
   fun a Оҙa hОҙa hunram u hu =>
     unramifiedQuadratic_units_are_norms k a Оҙa hОҙa hunram u huвҹ©

/-! ## In-repository Kummer and unit-filtration interfaces

Lemma 6.17 uses local Kummer surjectivity and the graded structure of the dyadic unit filtration.
Both interfaces are constructed below from in-repository proofs.  The surrounding
`DeepKummerData` assembly is developed in `GQ2/LocalKummer.lean`; its remaining inputs include
coprime averaging, the Hensel square criterion, graded duality, Lemma 6.10, and Lemma 6.11.
-/

/-- **Local Kummer theory, surjective half, formerly interface B12.**

For a finite extension `k/в„ҡвӮӮ`, the Kummer class map descends to an isomorphism
`k^Г—/(k^Г—)ВІ вү… HВ№(G_k, в„Ө/2)` (continuous cochain cohomology; `ОјвӮӮ вү… в„Ө/2`, canonical in
char 0).  This theorem exposes only surjectivity; injectivity is proved separately by
`Kummer.kummerClass_eq_zero_iff` (`[a] = 0 вҶ” IsSquare a`) via Mathlib's infinite Galois
correspondence.

Citation: **NSW [1], Ch. VI В§2 вҖ” Theorem (6.2.1) (Hilbert's Satz 90)
and the Kummer-sequence isomorphism `HВ№(G_K, Ој_n) вү… K^Г—/K^{Г—n}` displayed immediately after it
(electronic ed. p. 344), dual form Theorem (6.2.2)**; at `n = 2`.  Secondary: Serre, *Local
Fields* [7], Ch. XIV В§2 (p. 206).  Both verified verbatim against the cited PDFs; the audit
copies are not vendored in this repository.

The proof in `GQ2/KummerSurjectivity.lean` combines completing the square with the
KrullвҖ“Galois correspondence from `GQ2/KummerKrullBridge.lean`, where an open index-two subgroup
produces the required quadratic subextension.

Paper: В§6.3 (Lemma 6.17, "By HochschildвҖ“Serre and Kummer theory").
`docs/literature-axioms.md` B12. -/
theorem kummerClassK_surjective (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k] :
    Function.Surjective (kummerClassK k) :=
  KummerSurjectivity.kummerClassK_surjective' k

/-- **The dyadic unit filtration interface, formerly B13.**

Every finite extension `k/в„ҡвӮӮ` carries a `DyadicUnitFiltration` (`GQ2/UnitFiltration.lean`):
a uniformizer `ПҖ` (an element of maximal spectral norm `< 1` вҖ” discreteness of the value
group), the normalization `вҖ–2вҖ– = вҖ–ПҖвҖ–^e` (`e = v_k(2) вүҘ 1`), a residue degree `f вүҘ 1`, and
the graded counts of the unit filtration `U^{(i)} = 1 + рқ”ӯ_k^i`:
`#(U^{(0)}/U^{(1)}) = 2^f вҲ’ 1` and `#(U^{(i)}/U^{(i+1)}) = 2^f` for `i вүҘ 1`.

Citation: **Serre, *Local Fields* [7], Ch. IV В§2, Proposition 6** (verified verbatim against
the cited source, pp. 66вҖ“67; the audit copy is not vendored): "(a) `U_L/U_L^{(1)} = LМ„^*`;
(b) for `i вүҘ 1`, the group
`U^{(i)}/U^{(i+1)}` is canonically isomorphic to `рқ”ӯ_L^i/рқ”ӯ_L^{i+1}`, which is itself
isomorphic (non-canonically) to the additive group of the residue field `LМ„`" вҖ” read through
`#LМ„ = 2^f`, `#LМ„^Г— = 2^f вҲ’ 1`.  Uniformizer existence: Serre LF Ch. IвҖ“II (discrete
valuations, complete fields; standard).

Deviations (flagged, review-packet В§3): stated in spectral-norm vocabulary (no valuation
ring/residue field is constructed вҖ” the graded pieces enter through their cardinalities, the
form the multiplicity count consumes); the proposal's (F2) inertia-twist clause
(`Оё_g = (gвҖўПҖ)/ПҖ` acting on `gr_j` by `Оё_g^j`) is derivable from the exact `в„ҡМ„вӮӮ`-algebra action
and the `he` normalization, so it is deliberately not stored as a field.

Paper: В§6.3, eq. (93) (the display's own bracket "[7, Ch. XIV В§В§2вҖ“3]" is coarse вҖ” the
filtration is Ch. IV В§2).  `docs/literature-axioms.md` B13.

The definition delegates to `dyadicUnitFiltration'` in `GQ2/UnitFiltrationCounts.lean`, built on
`GQ2/UnitFiltrationTop.lean`; `Classical.choice` selects witnesses from the proved existence
lemmas.  The uniformizer comes from compactness of the
unit ball + an `O/2O` pigeonhole (no spectral-norm value formula); the residue field `O/рқ”Ә` is the
finite quotient of the valuation subring; and the graded counts are the explicit isomorphisms
`U^{(0)}/U^{(1)} вү… (O/рқ”Ә)ЛЈ` and `U^{(i)}/U^{(i+1)} вү… (O/рқ”Ә)вҒә`. -/
noncomputable def dyadicUnitFiltration (k : IntermediateField в„ҡ_[2] (AlgebraicClosure в„ҡ_[2]))
    [FiniteDimensional в„ҡ_[2] k] :
    DyadicUnitFiltration k :=
  dyadicUnitFiltration' k

end GQ2

